Parliament, Sunday 10 May 2020 – Plans to save the 2020 academic year, finalisation of the appointments of board members and strategic and annual performance plans of the various government departments are some of the many important issues scheduled for this week.
	
	Minister of Higher Education, Science and Technology, is on Thursday, 14 May 2020, scheduled to appear before a joint meeting of the National Assembly’s Portfolio Committee on Higher Education, Science and Technology and the National Council of Province’s Select Committee on Education, Technology, Sports, Arts and Culture, for a follow-up briefing on the plans to save the 2020 academic year.
	
	The Portfolio Committee on Communications and its Subcommittee are scheduled to finalise the processes on the appointments of board members to serve the Independent Communications Authority of South Africa (ICASA) Council and the Media Development and Diversity Agency (MDDA).
	
	At least 51 meetings of the Committees of the two Houses – The National Assembly and the National Council of Provinces - are scheduled to hold virtual oversight meetings this week.
	
	MONDAY, 11 MAY 2020:
	
	Standing Committee on Appropriations - Briefing by the Parliamentary Budget Office on the 2020 Appropriation Bill,
	
	Portfolio Committee on Transport - Briefing by the Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa (PRASA) on its 2020/2021 Corporate Plan, including briefing by the Minister and the PRASA Administrator on their plans to effect change at the entity within the 12- month contract of the Administrator,
	
	Portfolio Committee on Communications (Subcommittee) - Deliberations on the interviewed candidates for vacancies in the Independent Communications Authority of South Africa (ICASA) Council,
	
	Portfolio Committee on Communications (Subcommittee) - Shortlisting of candidates for the Media Development and Diversity Agency (MDDA) Board,
	
	Portfolio Committee on Communications - Consideration and adoption of report recommending candidates for appointment to the Independent Communications Authority of South Africa (ICASA) Council; and Consideration and adoption of the report recommending candidates to be shortlisted for interviews for the Media Development and Diversity Agency (MDDA) Board;
	
	TUESDAY, 12 MAY 2020 
	
	Joint Meeting: Portfolio Committee on Sports, Arts and Culture and Select Committee on Education and Technology, Sports, Arts and Culture - Briefing by the Department of Sports, Arts and Culture on the 2020/21 Annual Performance Plan and 2020/25 Strategic Plan,
	
	Portfolio Committee on Human Settlements, Water and Sanitation - Briefing by the Office of the Auditor-General on the Audit Outcomes of the 2018/19 Annual Reports and Financial Statements of the Department of Water and Sanitation and the Trans- Caledon Tunnel Authority: Analysis, assessment and review of the work of water boards in executing their mandate – achievements, challenges and recommendations; Analysis, assessment and review of the 2020/21 Annual Performance Plan in respect of whether it addresses challenges to rectify the transgressions contained in the audit outcomes of the 2018/19 Annual Report and Financial Statements of the Department of Water and Sanitation and Entities; Briefing by the Department of Water and Sanitation on its 2018/19 Annual Report and Financial Statements],
	
	Joint Standing Committee on the Financial Management of Parliament - Briefing on the Strategic Plan and strategic priorities of the Sixth Parliament],
	
	Joint Meeting: Portfolio Committee on Basic Education and Select Committee on Education and Technology, Sports, Arts and Culture - Budget Review on Budget Vote 16: Basic Education (2020/21) (incl. Sector Plan, Annual Performance Plan and Strategic Plan) by the South African Council for Educators (SACE),
	
	
	Joint Meeting: Standing Committee on Public Accounts and Portfolio Committee on Public Enterprises - Briefing by the Minister of Public Enterprises and the Business Rescue Practitioners on the business rescue plans for SAA and SA Express Airways,
	
	WEDNESDAY, 13 MAY 2020 
	
	Portfolio Committee on Health - Briefing by the Auditor-General of South Africa (AGSA) on their analysis and assessment of the Department of Health’s Strategic Plan, Annual Performance Plan and Budget,
	
	Joint Meeting: Portfolio Committee on Police and Select Committee on Security and Justice - Budget hearing briefings: Civilian Secretariat for Police (CSP) and Independent Police Investigative (IPID),
	
	Portfolio Committee on Public Service and Administration - Briefing by the DPSA on the number of suspended employees over the past years and cost of suspension of the public servants. Briefing by Government Pension Administration Agency on whether or not the Steinhoff debacle impacted on the pension fund; and how much financial impact was caused and measures introduced to mitigate such incidences to occur in future. Briefing by the Government Employees Medical Scheme on the funding model of government employees medical aid and reasons for early exhaustion of funds subjecting employees to pay from their own pockets.
	
	Portfolio Committee on Trade and Industry - Joint briefing by the IDC and the NEF on their contribution to government’s COVID-19 response,
	
	Portfolio Committee on Communications - Briefing by the Department of Communications and Digital Technologies (Department) on its 2020/21 Annual Performance Plan and Budget; Briefing by the South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC) on its 2020/21 Annual Performance Plan and Budget],
	
	THURSDAY, 14 MAY 2020 
	
	Joint Meeting: Portfolio Committee on Police and Select Committee on Security and Justice - Budget hearings briefing: Private Security Industry Regulatory Authority (PSIRA),
	
	Portfolio Committee on Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs - Adoption of the report on the Budget Vote],
	
	Joint Meeting: Portfolio on Employment and Labour and Select Committee on Trade and Industry, Economic Development, Tourism, Employment and Labour - Briefing by Nedlac and Productivity SA, on their Strategic Plans and Annual Performance Plans for 2020/21 South African Tourism on budget Vote and Annual Performance plans 2020/21],
	
	Joint Meeting: Portfolio Committee on Sports, Arts and Culture and Select Committee on Education and Technology, Sports, Arts and Culture - Briefing by the Department of Sports and Recreation on the Annual Performance and Strategic Plan,
	
	Portfolio Committee on Communications - Briefing by Government Communication and Information System (GCIS) on its 2020/21 Annual Performance Plan and Budget; Briefing by the South African Post Office (SAPO) on its 2020/21 Annual Performance Plan and Budget,
	
	FRIDAY, 15 MAY 2020 
	
	Portfolio Committee on Higher Education, Science and Technology and Select Committee on Education, Technology, Sports, Arts and Culture - Briefing by the Department of Science and Innovation (DSI) on Strategic Plan 2020 – 2025 and Annual Performance Plan 2020/21,
	
	Portfolio Committee on Human Settlements, Water and Sanitation - Briefing by the entities supporting the work of the Department of Water and Sanitation on its Annual Report and Financial statements for 2018/19: Water Research Commission; Briefing by Water Boards on the 2018/19 Annual Report and Financial Statements: 2 Water Boards: Bloem; Magalies,
	
	Portfolio Committee on Women, Youth and Persons with Disabilities - Briefing by the National Youth Development Agency on Annual Performance Plan for 2020/21 and Strategic Plan and Budget for 2020/2025], 12:00- 15:00
	
	Portfolio Committee on Justice and Correctional Services - Briefing by the South African Human Rights Commission on its Strategic Plan, APP and Budget 2020/21. Briefing by the Special Investigative Unit on its Strategic Plan, APP and Budget 2020/21,
	
	Joint Meeting: Portfolio Committee on Environment, Forestry and Fisheries and Select Committee on Land Reform, Environment, Mineral Resources and Energy - Briefing by the Auditor General on the overall status of the Environment, Forestry and Fisheries Portfolio as well as record review 2020/21; Briefing by the Department of Environment, Forestry and Fisheries on its Strategic Plans and Annual Performance Plan for 2020/2021 (Budget Vote):32,
	
	SATURDAY, 16 MAY 2020 
	
	Portfolio Committee on Justice and Correctional Services - Briefing by the Public Protector South Africa on its Strategic Plan, APP and Budget 2020/21,
	
	Portfolio Committee on Communications - Briefing by the Independent Communications Authority of South Africa (ICASA) on its 2020/21 Annual Performance Plan and Budget,
	
	For a full list of the Committees, visit Parliament’s website www.parliament.gov.za
	
